Program: Great Lives
Title: Robert Louis Stevenson
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0076rh9
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 25 Sep 2015
Series of biographical discussions with Francine Stock. Poet Douglas Dunn nominates Robert Louis Stevenson, explaining that the first book he ever read was Treasure Island and that he has loved its author ever since. Biographer Claire Harman fills in the details of a short but energetic life that began in Edinburgh and ended on the island of Samoa. Show less